	        Send us your pictures   ·  Send us your stories Police are investigating the murder of a 42-year-old man who was shot dead in Belhar, Cape Town, on Wednesday. Police spokesperson Sergeant Noloyiso Rwexana said that the man was shot at 16:30 on Chestnut Road. "According to reports a 42-year-old man... sustained multiple gunshot wounds to his body. SAPS detectives are following up on leads to bring those involved to book," she said. In February, News24 reported that a 22-year-old man was shot in the same area in a possible gang-related shooting. However, this could not be confirmed by the police. Anyone with information about the shooting should contact Crime Stop on 08600 10111. 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.  